Share Quick Text

You can share quick text with users, public groups, and more. The way you share quick text in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience is different.

In Salesforce Classic, you can share individual quick text messages. In Lightning Experience, share quick text using folders.

Use folders to create unique sets of quick text messages for different business units. Create separate folders of quick text for your service and sales divisions, and then share each folder with the users in that division. Folders help you organize your quick text and give users a tailored list of quick text messages to work with.

You can also share an individual quick text record in Salesforce Classic with other users or groups.

See Also: Design Your Quick Text Strategy, Create Sharing Rules
title: Service Cloud: Sharing Quick Text
